Description: Upper body sherd of East Greek grey ware large pottery vessel, possibly a krater or dinos; brownish grey fabric with mica inclusions; dark grey slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Modern inscription 'Hera' on the interior indicates findspot.
Possibly from same vessel as 1965,0930.415 and 433.
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (pl. 22.1.1)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.020)
